Unilever Says Offer Period for Preference Shares Starts Tomorrow

-- B y   M a r t i j n   v a n   d e r   S t a r r e
-- 
2011-09-19T05:37:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-19/unilever-says-offer-period-for-preference-shares-starts-tomorrow.html
Unilever, the maker of Lipton tea,
offered to repurchase its 6 and 7 percent cumulative preference
shares after its shareholders approved the buyback on Sept. 16.  Unilever will pay holders of 6 and 7 percent cumulative
preference shares 806 euros and 940 euros apiece, respectively,
it said in a newspaper advertisement published in Het
Financieele Dagblad today. The tender period starts tomorrow and
ends on Oct. 18, Unilever said in a newspaper advertisement
published in Het Financieele Dagblad today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Martijn van der Starre at 
 vanderstarre@bloomberg.net  